<item>
            <title>[SPARK-53054] The Scala Spark Connect DataFrameReader does not use the correct default format</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-53054</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As documented in &lt;a href=&quot;https://spark.apache.org/docs/3.5.6/sql-data-sources-load-save-functions.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Generic Load/Save Functions - Spark 3.5.6 Documentation&lt;/a&gt;, and similar to Spark Classic and the Python Spark Connect, Scala Spark Connect&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;DataFrameReader&lt;/tt&gt; should default to the format set via the &lt;tt&gt;spark.sql.sources.default&lt;/tt&gt; config.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Currently&lt;/b&gt;: &lt;tt&gt;spark.read.load(&quot;...&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt; throws&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: The source format must be specified.&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expected&lt;/b&gt;: &lt;tt&gt;spark.read.load(&quot;...&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt; uses the format specified via &lt;tt&gt;spark.sql.sources.default&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
